CSAM offers unique advantages, including the ability to work with a wide range of materials, reduced thermal stress, and improved material properties. It plays a crucial role in aerospace, automotive, and other industries, enabling the production of complex, high-performance components with enhanced durability and reduced material waste. The importance of cold spray additive manufacturing lies in its potential to transform industries by enabling cost-effective, rapid, and precise fabrication of critical components while opening the door to new design possibilities and applications.
<br>
<br>
<b> Our current directions include:</b>
<ul>
<li> <b> Multifield modeling framework for polymer metallization. </b> </li>
<li> <b> Explorations of novel surface structures, design and development of multifunctional smart surfaces. </b> 
<li> <b> Multi-scale additive manufacturing of smart and self-powered surfaces on polymer substrates. </b> </li>




